file: crates/ctx-cage/tests/cli.rs
behavior: Tests `ctx_cage::cli::resolve_mode`'s pure logic for turning `Cli` flag combinations into a `Mode`, covering self-test, inline task, task-file, interactive default, and spend/conflict gating.
edit_notes:
  - Mirrors the `Cli`/`Mode`/`ResolveError`/`SelfTestKind`/`TaskFlags`/`SpendFlags` shapes defined in ctx_cage::cli; update tests if any field or variant changes.
  - task_file_is_read_from_disk is the only test touching the filesystem, via a unique tempdir path per-process/counter to avoid collisions across parallel test runs.
  - base() helper avoids unwrap/expect per workspace lint rule; test bodies still use expect/expect_err freely.
functions:
invariants:
  - resolve_mode(cli, allow_spend) blocks with ResolveError::NotAllowed when a billed mode (interactive default or inline task) is requested without allow_spend=true.
  - Combining task with task_file, self_test, or interactive yields ResolveError::Conflict.
external_deps: